"Hashimoto K.","Recent advances in the catalytic properties of metastable materials",1997,"Materials Science and Engineering A","226-228",,,"891","899",,,,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-0042325378&partnerID=40&md5=169473b9ce524c0c85e9d48635ee39aa","Institute for Materials Research, Tohoku University, Sendai 980-77, Japan","Hashimoto, K., Institute for Materials Research, Tohoku University, Sendai 980-77, Japan","New catalysts and electrocatalysts which are amorphous alloys themselves or prepared from amorphous and other metastable alloys are reviewed in this paper. The most important characteristic of metastable materials including amorphous and nanocrystalline alloys from the chemical point of view is the homogeneous single phase nature consisting of a variety of elements, whose concentrations sometimes exceed the solubility limits at equilibrium. For the enhancement of the activity various treatments are carried out before catalytic reaction, such as oxidation-reduction and selective dissolution of alloy constituents. For example, after immersion in HF, amorphous Cu-Zr alloys show higher activity than amorphous Cu-Ti alloys for dehydrogenation of 2-propanol and hydration of acrylonitrile. This is due to dissolution of smaller amounts of titanium from Cu-Ti alloys than dissolution of zirconium from Cu-Zr alloys in HF, since the corrosion resistance of titanium in HF is higher than zirconium. The catalysts prepared from some amorphous nickel alloys are most effective for methanation of CO2 at atmospheric pressure. Amorphous nickel-refractory metal alloys are the best cathode materials for electrolytic hydrogen evolution. The catalyst for CO2 methanation and the electrode for electrolytic hydrogen evolution are used for building a CO2 recycling plant to avoid global warming and to supply abundant energy. © 1997 Elsevier Science S.A.","Amorphous alloy; Catalyst; CO2 methanation; CO2 recycling; Electrocatalyst; Hydrogen evolution; Mechanical milling; Nanocrystalline substance","Amorphous alloys; Carbon dioxide; Catalyst activity; Dehydrogenation; Dissolution; Electrochemical electrodes; Methanation; Milling (machining); Nanostructured materials; Oxidation; Recycling; Electrocatalysts; Catalysts",,,,,,"Hara, M., Hashimoto, K., Masumoto, T., (1980) Electrochim. Acta, 25, p. 1215; Hara, M., Hashimoto, K., Masumoto, T., (1983) J. Non-cryst. Solids, 54, p. 85; Kumagai, N., Samata, Y., Kawashima, A., Asami, K., Hashimoto, K., (1987) J. Appl. Electrochem., 17, p. 347; Kumagai, N., Samata, Y., Jikihara, S., Kawashima, A., Asami, K., Hashimoto, K., (1988) Mater. Sci. Eng., 99, p. 489; Enyo, M., Yamazaki, T., Kai, K., Suzuki, K., (1983) Electrochim. Acta, 28, p. 1573; Machida, K., Enyo, M., Adachi, G., Shiokawa, J., (1984) Electrochim. Acta, 29, p. 807; Kawashima, A., Hashimoto, K., (1982) Rapidly Quenched Metals, p. 1427. , T. Masumoto and K. Suzuki (eds.), The Japan Institute of Metals, Sendai; Hayakawa, Y., Kawashima, A., Asami, K., Hashimoto, K., (1992) J. Appl. Electrochem., 22, p. 1017; Komiyama, H., Yokoyama, A., Inoue, H., Masumoto, T., Kimura, H., (1980) Sci. Rep. Res. Inst. Tohoku Univ., A28, p. 217; Yokoyama, A., Komiyama, H., Inoue, H., Masumoto, T., Kimura, H., (1981) J. Catal., 68, p. 355; Yokoyama, A., Komiyama, H., Inoue, H., Masumoto, T., Kimura, H., (1981) Scr. Metall., 15, p. 365; Schloegl, R., (1985) Rapidly Quenched Metals, p. 1723. , S. Steeb and H. Warlimont (eds.), Elsevier, Amsterdam; Yoon, C., Cocke, D.L., (1986) J. Non-cryst. Solids, 79, p. 217; Shibata, M., Masumoto, T., (1987) Preparation of Catalysts IV, p. 353. , B. Delmon, P. Grange, P.A. Jacobs and G. Poncelet (eds.), Elsevier, Amsterdam; Molnár, Á., Smith, G.V., Bartók, M., (1989) Adv. Catal., 36, p. 329; Baiker, A., (1989) Faraday Discuss. Chem. Soc., 87, p. 239; Somorjai, G.A., (1978) Catal. Rev. Sci. Eng., 18, p. 173; Smith, G.V., Brower, W.E., Matyaszczyk, M.S., Pettit, T.L., (1981) Proc. 7th Int. Cong. Catalysis, p. 355. , T. Seiyama and K. Tanabe (eds.), Elsevier, New York; Brower, W.E., Matyaszczyk, M.S., Pettit, T.L., Smith, G.V., (1983) Nature (London), 301, p. 497; Smith, G.V., Zahraa, O., Molnár, Á., Kahn, M.M., Lichter, B., Brower, W.E., (1983) J. Catal., 83, p. 238; Smith, G.V., Molnár, Á., Kahn, M.M., Ostrgad, D., Yoshida, N., (1986) J. Catal., 98, p. 502; Komiyama, H., Yokoyama, A., Inoue, H., Masumoto, T., Kimura, H., (1980) Sci. Rep. Res. Inst. Tohoku Univ., A28, p. 217; Yokoyama, A., Komiyama, H., Inoue, H., Masumoto, T., Kimura, H.M., (1981) Scr. Metall., 15, p. 365; Gasser, D., Baker, A., (1989) Appl. Catal., 48, p. 279; Yamashita, H., Yoshikawa, M., Funabiki, T., Yoshida, S., (1984) J. Chem. Soc. Faraday Trans., 1 (80), p. 1435; Yokoyama, A., Komiyama, H., Inoue, H., Masumoto, T., Kimura, H.M., (1983) Chem. Lett., p. 195; Yokoyama, A., Komiyama, H., Inoue, H., Masumoto, T., Kimura, H.M., (1985) Chem. Lett., p. 66; Shimogami, Y., Komiyama, H., Inoue, H., Masumoto, T., Kimura, H.M., (1988) Chem. Engng. Jpn., 21, p. 293; Katona, T., Hegedus, Z., Kopasz, C., Molnár, Á., Bartok, M., (1990) Catal. Lett., 5, p. 351; Molnár, Á., Katona, T., Bartok, M., Valga, K., (1991) J. Molec. Catal., 64, p. 41; Molnár, Á., Katona, T., Bartok, M., Perczel, I.V., Hegedus, Z., Kopasz, C., (1991) Mater. Sci. Eng., A134, p. 1083; Katona, T., Molnár, Á., Bartok, M., (1994) Mater. Sci. Eng., A181-182, p. 1095; Katona, T., Molnár, Á., (1995) J. Catal., 153, p. 333; Kumagai, N., Samata, Y., Kawashima, A., Asami, K., Hashimoto, K., (1987) J. Appl. Electrochem., 17, p. 347; Funabiki, T., Yamashita, H., Yase, M., Omatsu, T., Yoshida, S., (1993) Bull. Chem. Soc. Jpn., 66, p. 2133; Wakuda, K., Habazaki, H., Kawashima, A., Asami, K., Hashimoto, K., (1993) Sci. Rep. Res. Inst. Tohoku Univ., A38 (1), pp. 76-87; Habazaki, H., Tada, T., Wakuda, K., Kawashima, A., Asami, K., Hashimoto, K., (1993) Corrosion, Electrochemistry and Catalysis of Metastable Metals and Intermetallics, pp. 393-404. , C.R. Clayton and K. Hashimoto (eds.), The Electrochemical Society; Shimamura, K., Yoshida, T., Yamasaki, M., Komori, M., Habazaki, H., Akiyaraa, E., Kawashima, A., Hashimoto, K., (1997) Mater. Sci. Eng., , in press; Takahashi, T., Kai, T., (1995) Kagaku Kougaku Ronbunshu, 21, p. 961; Baiker, A., Gasser, D., (1989) J. Chem. Soc. Faraday Trans., 1 (85), p. 999; Coteron, A., Hayhurst, A.N., (1993) Appl. Catal., 101, p. 151; Mulas, G., Conti, L., Scano, G., Schiffini, L., Cocco, G., (1994) Mater. Sci. Eng., A181-182, p. 1085; Cocco, G., Mulas, G., Pintore, M., Piliu, G., Schiffini, L., (1993) Proc. Int. Conf. Structural Applications of Mechanical Alloying, p. 425. , J.J. de Barbadillo, F.H. Froe and R.B. Schwarz (eds.), ASM International, Materials Park, Ohio; Cocco, G., Mulas, G., Schiffini, L., (1995) Mater. Trans. JIM, 36, p. 150; Kita, H., (1966) J. Electrochem. Soc., 113, p. 1095; Kita, H., Honda, M., (1970) DENKI KAGAKU, 38, p. 17; Kawashima, A., Habazaki, H., Akiyama, E., Hashimoto, K., (1997) Mater. Sci. Eng., , in press; Brown, D.E., Mahmood, M.N., Man, M.C.M., Turner, A.K., (1984) Electrochim. Acta, 29, p. 1551; Brown, D.E., Hall, S.M., Mahmood, M.M., Man, M.C.M., Turner, A.K., Wood, D., Anderson, S., (1982) Proc. Electrocatalysis, 82 (2), p. 145. , W.E. O'Grady, P.N. Ross Jr. and F.G. Will (eds.), The Electrochemical Society, Pennington, NJ; Schulz, R., Huot, J.Y., Trudeau, M.L., Dignard-Bailey, L., Yan, Z.H., Jin, S., Lamarre, A., Van Neste, A., (1994) J. Mater. Res., 9, p. 2998; Hashimoto, K., (1994) Mater. Sci. Eng., A179-A180, p. 27","Hashimoto, K.; Institute for Materials Research, Tohoku University, Sendai 980-77, Japan",,,,,,,,09215093,,,,"English","Mater. Sci. Eng. A",Article,Scopus,2-s2.0-0042325378
